import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="Species", y="Body_Mass__g_", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    ax.axhline(y=data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="Species", y="Flipper_Length__mm_", data=data, ci=None)
    ax.axhline(y=data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Beak_Depth__mm_', hue='Sex', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data.groupby('Sex')['Beak_Depth__mm_'].median()['FEMALE'], color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Female Median: {:.2f}'.format(data.groupby('Sex')['Beak_Depth__mm_'].median()['FEMALE']))
    plt.axvline(data.groupby('Sex')['Beak_Depth__mm_'].median()['MALE'], color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Male Median: {:.2f}'.format(data.groupby('Sex')['Beak_Depth__mm_'].median()['MALE']))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak depth for male and female penguins?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
